Jeep Grand Cherokee  Limited w/ nearly all the options available for this year and model.  Here is a list of what this car has:   - 5.7 Liter V-8 Hemi  - Deluxe wheels in near new condition (18")  - 4 great condition Michelin Latitude tires with LOTS of tread life left!  - Newly replaced spare tire  - Both AC and heating work great!  - Climate control heating and cooling with separate controls for driver and passenger  - Rear seating area heating and A/C vents  - Roof rack with cross bars  - High end factory tow package with the optional transmission cooler and upgraded alternator,  Includes trailer wiring and tow/haul button on the dash to reconfigure the drive train for when towing heavy loads.  - Electronically controlled low range for easy switchover  - Leather heated power seats in the front and leather seats in the back (good condition!)  - Rear seat has pull down armrests between the passengers  - Rear seats fold down easily to expand the cargo area.  - Tilt steering wheel with factory Jeep wheel cover (comfy!)  - Regular maintenance including recent fluid changes for transmission, transfer case and both differentials  - No accidents or damage other than some parking lot dings and scratches  What's wrong with it?   - Not much.  As mentioned there are some dings and scratches from the parking lots  - Radio display just recently died (but the radio works fine) coinciding with the check engine light coming on.  My mechanic tells me the code says electrical / wiring issue.  Probably the radio!  I do have a Blaupunkt replacement radio which I will include.  It has been a great car!  I have had a number of Grand Cherokees many going to almost 300,000 miles without any issues.  This should continue to give years of great service.
